		Data extracted is based on the the first arrest date.							
									
		The number of custody records do not equal the number of individuals. For example, an individual may have been arrested twice within the time							
		period stated.							
									
		The offence title does not indicate the outcome.  For example, some offence titles may have resulted in 'no further action'.							
									
		Age has been provided using  the 'Age at Arrest' field.							
									
		In accordance with the request, the data was restricted to the following CJS codes:							
									
		VG24003	Begging and wandering abroad						
		VG24005	Begging in a public place						
		VG24013	Begging in a public place - second or subsequent occasion						
		VG24015	Begging and wandering abroad - second / subsequent occasion						
		VG24017	Lodging in a barn / outhouse / unoccupied building / open air - Vagrancy Act 1824						
		VG24018	Vagrant - being found in or upon enclosed premises						
		VG24021	Gather / collect alms / charitable donations by false pretence / fraud						
		VG24047	Persistently beg in a public place ( second or subsequent offence ) - Vagrancy Act 1824						
									
		In CONNECT, offences can also be recorded under a 'Reason for Arrest' (RFA).  For CONNECT data, the following RFA's were additionally searched for:							
		Begging							
		Begging - Persistent							
		Found on enclosed premises.							
									
		Note that a template was mentioned in the above request.  This has not been seen by the data analyst so the response has been constructed as follows:							
									
		There are 4 reports attached which are as follows:							
									
		Report 1 - Arrests  under the Vagrancy Act 1824  - 1 April 2019 - 31 March 2023							
									
		The custody records had at least one relevant offence entered on the custody record.							
									
		Report 2 - Detainees Charged for Offences under the Vagrancy Act 1824 - 1 April 2019 - 31 March 2023							
									
		The custody records shown with a 'charge' had at least one relevant offence with one of the following latest disposals:							
		Charge							
		Charged and Bailed To Court							
		Charged and Detained For Court							
		To Court (Postal Requisitions)							
									
		 Report 3 - Reasons for Arrest for Age Groups 16-17 and 18-25 for custody records with offences under Vagrancy Act 1824 Apr 19 - Mar 23							
									
		The report shows the 'First Reason for Arrest (RFA)'  (NSPIS) / 'RFA Offence Description' (CONNECT) for the arrests of those falling into the age ranges 							
		16-17 or 18-25 where there has been at least one relevant offence recorded on the custody record under the Vagrancy Act 1824.							
		It should be noted that a detainee may have been arrested for multiple offences and/or arrested for other offences not relating to those under the 							
		Vagrancy Act 1824.							
									
		 Report 4 - Offence Titles for Charges for Age Groups 16-17 and 18-25 for offences under Vagrancy Act 1824 Apr 19 - Mar 23							
									
		The report lists the offences where those aged 16-17 or 18-25 have been charged with an offence falling under the Vagrancy Act 1824.							
		See the notes under 'Report 2' for additional information.  							
		All offence titles that received a charge have been shown in this report for the specified age ranges over the requested time period.							


